-- Nokia CEO Elop to move to Microsoft, chairman to take over
-- 
-- Tue Sep 3, 2013 12:00am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2013/09/03/us-nokia-ceo-idUSBRE98204820130903

 

 HELSINKI  (Reuters) - Nokia ( NOK1V.HE ) said its chief executive, Stephen Elop, will move to Microsoft Corp ( MSFT.O ) when the deal to acquire Nokia's handset business is closed. 
 Nokia board chairman Risto Siilasmaa will take over CEO duties while the Finnish firm is looking for a new CEO. Elop was hired as Nokia CEO in 2010 from Microsoft. (Reporting by  Terhi Kinnunen ; Editing by Matt Driskill)